## Rule 2 — Use specialized tools instead of Shell for file ops

Shell invocations of file-search / file-read / file-edit utilities failed or
produced noisy output in 75 cases last week. Use the tool purpose-built for
the job.

| Instead of Shell… | Use the tool |
|---|---|
| `find <dir> -name "*.kt"` | `Glob` with `glob_pattern: "**/*.kt"` |
| `grep -r "pattern" <dir>` / `rg "pattern"` | `Grep` with `pattern` + `glob` / `type` filter |
| `cat file.kt` / `head -40 file.kts` / `tail -n 20 log.txt` | `Read` (with `offset`/`limit` if needed) |
| `sed -i 's/old/new/g' file` | `StrReplace` with `replace_all: true` |
| `echo "content" > file` or heredoc-to-file | `Write` |

### Concrete anti-patterns from last week

```bash
# BAD: shelling out to find files
find /Users/ajo130/code/mpe.capability.clickstream/Android -name "*.kt" | head -20

# GOOD: Glob tool
# { "glob_pattern": "**/*.kt", "target_directory": "/Users/ajo130/code/mpe.capability.clickstream/Android" }
```

```bash
# BAD: grep -r + cat pipelines for cross-file searches
grep -r "Timber\|Log\." /Users/ajo130/code/mpe.capability.clickstream/Android --include="*.kt" -l

# GOOD: Grep tool
# { "pattern": "Timber|Log\\.", "path": "/Users/ajo130/code/mpe.capability.clickstream/Android", "glob": "*.kt", "output_mode": "files_with_matches" }
```

```bash
# BAD: cat with head slicing
cat Android/clickstream/build.gradle.kts | head -40

# GOOD: Read tool
# { "path": ".../build.gradle.kts", "limit": 40 }
```

```bash
# BAD: sed -i for code edits
sed -i '' 's/onCarouselCardSettled/onCarouselCardViewed/g' components/doorway/impl/src/main/kotlin/.../DoorwayView.kt

# GOOD: StrReplace with replace_all
# { "path": ".../DoorwayView.kt", "old_string": "onCarouselCardSettled", "new_string": "onCarouselCardViewed", "replace_all": true }
```

```bash
# BAD: echo > README.md for new file creation
mkdir -p /Users/ajo130/code/agent-manager && echo "# agent-manager" > README.md

# GOOD: mkdir in Shell (creating dir structure is legitimate Shell work),
#       then Write tool for the file
```

> **Reserve Shell for real shell work**: `git` operations, `gradle`, `adb`,
> `gh`, `mise`, process management, and command chaining/piping that has no
> tool equivalent.

